            <p>

					+<lb/>
ΕΝΤΟΙCΑΓΙΟΙCΤΟΠΟΙC<lb/>
ΜΝΗCΘΗΙΛΑΡΙΑ<lb/>
ΗΥΞΑΤΟCΥΝΚΛΗΤΙΟC<lb/>
ΚΕΕΙCΑΚΟΥCΟΝ<lb/>
	ΑΜΗΝ<lb/>
	   +
</p>
         </div>
         <div type="edition"
              ana="#b1"
              subtype="transcription"
              xml:id="hamm0035.transcription"
              corresp="#hamm0035.diplomatic #hamm0035.translation">
            <p> Ἐν τοῖς ἀγίοις τόποις<lb/> μνησθῇ Ἱλαρία.<lb/> Ηὗξατο Ϲυνκλήτιος<lb/>
                  Κ<add>ύρι</add>ε εἰσάκουσον.<lb/> Ἀμήν. </p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation"
              ana="#b1"
              xml:id="hamm0035.translation"
              corresp="#hamm0035.diplomatic #hamm0035.transcription">
            <p>
               <rs type="formula">In these holy places </rs> may <persName xml:lang="grc " ref="persons.xml#hamm0035p01">Hilaria </persName> be remembered. <persName xml:lang="la " ref="persons.xml#hamm0035p02">Syncletius </persName> uttered this prayer: hearken, O Lord! Amen.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Slab of grayish-white marble. Prominently placed near the center of the hall, the script is calligraphic and the inscription decoratively framed. Frame is 51 cm by 71 cm and lines are 58 cm long.</p>
         </div>
